ffe]] (born 1950)\n\n===Weightlifters===\n*[[David Morgan (weightlifter)|David Morgan]] (born 1964), three times Olympian, three times masters world champion and holder of three world records\n\n===Wrestlers===\n{{div col}}\n*[[Mandrews|Mark 'Mandrews' Andrews]] (born 1992)\n*[[Sandy Orford]] (1911\u20131986)\n*[[Mason Ryan]] (born 1982)\n*[[Adrian Street]] (born 1940)\n*[[Rob Terry]] (born 1980)\n*[[Don Vines]] (1932\u20131989)\n*[[Orig Williams]] (1931\u20132009)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Trade union leaders==\n{{div col}}\n*[[William Abraham (trade unionist)|William Abraham]] (1842\u20131922), also known as Mabon\n*[[William Brace]] (1865\u20131947)\n*[[Moss Evans]] (1925\u20132002)\n*[[Jim Griffiths]] (1890\u20131975)\n*[[Vernon Hartshorn]] (1872\u20131931)\n*[[Arthur Horner (trade unionist)|Arthur Horner]] (1894\u20131968)\n*[[Clive Jenkins]] (1926\u20131999)\n*[[Will Paynter]] (1903\u20131984)\n*[[Thomas Richards (Welsh politician)|Thomas Richards]] (1859\u20131931)\n*[[J. H. Thomas|James Henry Thomas]] (1874\u20131949)\n*[[Huw T. Edwards]] (1892\u20131970)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Writers==\nFor Welsh writers, see:\n*[[List of Welsh writers]]\n*[[List of Welsh language authors]]\n*[[List of Welsh language poets (6th century to c.1600)]]\n*[[List of Welsh women writers]]\n\n==Other notables==\n{{div col}}\n*[[Helen Adams]] (born 1978), runner-up in ''[[Big Brother 2001 (UK)|Big Brother 2]]'' (2001)\n*[[Charles Ashburner]] (born 1969), Chief Executive Trustee of the Flag Institute, owner of MrFlag brand\n*[[Seymour Berry, 1st Baron Buckland]] (1877\u20131928), industrialist\n*[[Michael Bogdanov]] (1938\u20132017), theatre director\n*[[Emrys G. Bowen|E. G. Bowen]] (1900\u20131983), geographer \n*[[Betsi Cadwaladr]] (1789\u20131860), [[Crimean War]] nurse\n*[[Gwladys ferch Dafydd Gam]] (d. 1454), ''Seren y Fenni'' (''Star of Abergavenny'')\n*[[Rees Davies]] (1938\u20132005), historian\n*[[John Dee]] (born 1527), alchemist\n*[[Samuel Ifor Enoch]] (1914\u20132001), theologian\n*[[John Gwenogvryn Evans]] (1852\u20131930), palaeographic expert\n*[[Timothy John Evans]] (1924\u20131950), hanged for the murder of wife and daughter, due to a [[miscarriage of justice]], but posthumously pardoned\n*[[Geoffrey of Monmouth]] (c.1100\u20131155), churchman and historian\n*[[Peter Havard-Williams]] (1922\u20131995), librarian educator\n*[[George Jeffreys, 1st Baron Jeffreys]] (1648\u20131689), hanging judge\n*[[Ernest Jones]] (1879\u20131958), psychoanalyst\n*[[Walter Map]] (c.1137\u20131209), medieval raconteur\n*[[Howard Marks]] (1945\u22122016), international drug-smuggler and author\n*[[Angus McBean]] (1904\u20131990), photographer\n*[[Godfrey Morgan, 1st Viscount Tredegar]] (1831\u20131913), Member of Parliament, land-owner and benefactor\n*[[Henry Morgan]] (c.1635\u20131688), privateer\n*Edward Williams (1747\u20131826), a.k.a. [[Iolo Morganwg]], antiquarian\n*Marcus Piggott (born 1971), fashion photographer, half of duo [[Mert and Marcus]] \n*[[William Price (doctor)|Dr William Price]] (1800\u20131893), eccentric physician\n*[[Arwel Richards]] (born 1982), columnist and businessman\n*[[Bartholomew Roberts]] (1682\u20131722), pirate (Black Bart or Barti Ddu)\n*[[William Salesbury]] (c.1520\u2013c.1600), lexicographer, phonetician and comparative linguist\n*[[James Sommerin]] (born c. 1978), chef\n*[[John Tabatabai]] (born 1987), professional poker player\n*[[Robert Vaughan (antiquary)|Robert Vaughan]] (c.1592\u201316 May 1667), antiquary\n*[[Bryn Williams]] (born 1977), chef\n*[[John Tudno Williams]] (born 1938), theologian\n*[[William Richard Williams (theologian)|William Richard Williams]] (1896\u20131962), theologian\n*[[Glyn Wise]] (born 1988), ''[[Big Brother (TV series)|Big Brother]]'' 2006 runner-up\n*[[Thomas Wynne]] (1627\u20131691), surgeon, [[Quaker]] and friend of [[William Penn]]\n*[[Mike Young (producer)|Mike Young]] (born 1945), TV producer\n*[[Andrew House]] (born 1965), President and Group CEO of [[Sony Computer Entertainment]] (2011\u20132017)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Wales}}\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[100 Welsh Heroes]]\n*[[Canadians of Welsh descent]]\n*[[List of people by nationality]]\n*[[List of Welsh Americans]]\n*[[List of Welsh women]]\n*[[Welsh American]]\n*[[Welsh Australian]]\n*[[Welsh Chilean]]\n*[[Welsh Italians]]\n*[[Welsh peers and baronets]]\n*''[[Y Wladfa]]''\n{{colend}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090208173645/http://welshicons.org.uk/html/famous_welsh.php Famous Welsh People on the Welsh Icons Site]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090208173432/http://welshicons.org.uk/html/sport.php Famous Welsh Sports People on the Welsh Icons Site]\n*[http://www.famouswelsh.com/Welsh-Actors/index.php Famous Welsh Actors]\n*[http://www.famouswelsh.com/Welsh-Musicians/index.php Famous Welsh Musicians]\n*[http://www.famouswelsh.com/Welsh-Writers/index.php Famous Welsh Writers]\n*[http://www.famouswelsh.com/Welsh-Artists/index.php Famous Welsh Artists]\n*[http://www.famouswelsh.com/Welsh-Science/index.php Famous Welsh Scientists]\n*[http://www.famouswelsh.com/Welsh-Business/index.php Famous Welsh Businessmen]\n*[http://www.famouswelsh.com/Welsh-History/index.php Famous Welsh In Myth and Historical]\n*[http://www.famouswelsh.com/Welsh-Sport/index.php Famous Welsh Sport Personalities]\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Welsh People}}\n[[Category:Lists of Welsh people| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of British people]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toSteve Jones(link changed toSteve Jones (Welsh presenter)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Welsh_people"}
