for the tour, the band was giving away their entire music catalog free as a digital download with purchase of top tier seating.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nodoubt.com/news/default.aspx?nid=20646&cmnt=1#s_comments_anchor |title=News : Receive No Doubt's Entire Digital Catalog For Free With Online Ticket Purchase |publisher=No Doubt |date= |accessdate=2011-03-27}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, No Doubt made an appearance on the television series ''[[Gossip Girl (TV series)|Gossip Girl]]'', playing a fictional band called \"Snowed Out\" in the episode \"[[Valley Girls (Gossip Girl)|Valley Girls]]\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nodoubt.com/news/default.aspx?nid=20605 |title=News : Gossip Girl Appearance Announced! |publisher=No Doubt |date=2009-02-26 |accessdate=2011-10-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714190757/http://nodoubt.com/news/default.aspx?nid=20605 |archive-date=2011-07-14 |url-status=dead }}</ref> They performed their cover version of the [[Adam and the Ants]] song \"[[Stand and Deliver (Adam and the Ants song)|Stand and Deliver]]\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Vena |first=Jocelyn |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1607156/20090317/no_doubt.jhtml |title=No Doubt Say They 'All Agreed' On 'Gossip Girl' Song - Music, Celebrity, Artist News |publisher=MTV |date=2009-03-17 |accessdate=2011-03-27}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn October 1999, Young proposed to his girlfriend Nina Kent on stage during a No Doubt concert.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=orEMNtAugBk |title=Adrian Young Proposes To Nina Onstage During No Doubt Show (10/10/1999) |publisher=[[YouTube]] |date=2011-01-16 |accessdate=2017-07-27}}</ref> They were married in January 2000. The couple had a son in 2002<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://popcrush.com/no-doubt-adrian-young-wife-baby-girl/ |title=No Doubt Drummer Adrian Young and Wife Nina Welcome Baby Girl |website=Popcrush.com |date= |accessdate=2017-07-27}}</ref> and a daughter in 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://celebritybabies.people.com/2011/06/14/no-doubt-adrian-young-welcomes-daughter-magnolia/ |title=Adrian Young Welcomes Daughter Magnolia Ren\u00e9e |publisher=People babies |date=2011-06-14 |accessdate=2011-10-31}}</ref> Young's two children have a cousin-like relationship with the other offspring of No Doubt band members, as the children often spend time together during concerts.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/music-festivals/6538824/no-doubt-interview-festival-tour-next-album-global-citizen |title=No Doubt Talks 2015 Festival Tour, 'Experimenting' For Next Album at Global Citizen |magazine=Billboard |date=2015-04-20 |accessdate=2017-07-27}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Bow Wow Wow}}\n\n{{No Doubt}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Young, Adrian}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American rock drummers]]\n[[Category:No Doubt members]]\n[[Category:Bow Wow Wow members]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Long Beach, California]]\n[[Category:20th-century American drummers]]\n[[Category:American male drummers]]\n[[Category:Dreamcar members]]\n[[Category:American musicians]]\n", "name_user": "TheEpistle", "label": "safe", "comment": "little tweaks", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adrian_Young"}
